radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: CT ABD & PELVIS W & W/O CONTRAST, ADDL SECTIONS
radiographic_examinations.findings: Bilateral small-to-moderate pleural effusions with associated compressive atelectasis, moderate steatosis of the liver, diffuse inflammatory peripancreatic stranding, peripancreatic fluid extending into the anterior pararenal spaces, no intra- or extra-hepatic biliary ductal dilatation, gallbladder normal with no gallstones, kidneys enhance symmetrically, collapsed stomach with feeding tube in proximal jejunum, small amount of stranding and fluid in the pelvis, scattered small mesenteric and retroperitoneal lymph nodes.
